                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            A landowner (<foreign>uṭaiyāṉ</foreign>) from Kuḷattūr installed copper images of different idols, including that of Tiruvātavūr-Nāyaṉār (Māṇikkavācakar). It seems to also have given lands to <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign>.
                        </summary> 
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p>No distinction between <foreign>e</foreign> and <foreign>ē</foreign>, <foreign>o</foreign> and <foreign>ō</foreign>.</p>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
